  "buggy_functions": ["video_detect_dmi_table"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "On the Acer TravelMate 5735Z, backlight brightness control does not work by default. The issue is that the device is missing from the DMI quirks table (video_detect_dmi_table) in drivers/acpi/video_detect.c that controls which backlight driver should be used. The device should be configured to use the native ACPI video backlight driver (intel_backlight), but without a DMI entry, it falls through to the autodetect logic which incorrectly selects the vendor driver or standard ACPI video driver. When users manually specify 'acpi_backlight=native' at boot, the native backlight works properly with more brightness levels (15-16 vs 5). The fix requires adding a DMI entry for this Acer model in the video_detect_dmi_table with the video_detect_force_native callback to force native backlight selection."
}

